	<div class="posts">
	<a name="1644642021286586688"></a>
    
    
    <p>
	<div style="clear:both;"></div><h2>Hazard Warning: Much Site Breakage</h2>
<p>I&rsquo;ve just noticed how much damage there is on the <a href="http://miser-theory.info/">Miser Project</a> site as a result of my transfer to an Apache server.&nbsp; The previous Windows server did not treat URLs as case-sensitive.&nbsp; On Linux, Apache servers are case-sensitive.&nbsp; This has made problems with cross-references within the site and into the site.&nbsp; I am slowly repairing the cross-references within the site.&nbsp; Bookmarks into the site may end up being broken.&nbsp; The difference is usually around changes in capitalization in URLs.&nbsp; </p>
<p>Fortunately, this is a relatively small site.&nbsp; I will be repair internal links and provide some&nbsp;redirects for frequently-attempted broken external links over time.&nbsp; For now, I just want to offer this warning.</p><div class="bjtags">Tags:  <a rel="tag" href="http://technorati.com/tag/orcmid">orcmid</a>, <a rel="tag" href="http://technorati.com/tag/Apache">Apache</a>, <a rel="tag" href="http://technorati.com/tag/case+sensitivity">case+sensitivity</a>, <a rel="tag" href="http://technorati.com/tag/broken+URLs">broken+URLs</a></div><div style="clear:both; padding-bottom:0.25em"></div>
    </p>
	<span class="byline">posted by orcmid
       at <a href="http://miser-theory.info/astraendo/pn/2007/05/hazard-warning-much-site-breakage-i.asp">5/02/2007 05:07:00 PM</a></span>
	
